00:35:13,669 --> 00:35:14,727
That one.

274
00:35:21,076 --> 00:35:22,668
That one.

275
00:35:29,818 --> 00:35:31,285
That's the Tuta.

276
00:35:40,429 --> 00:35:41,487
And that one?

277
00:35:42,864 --> 00:35:47,801
That one that sounds like a cry?
It's the ¡*little widow

278
00:36:00,816 --> 00:36:02,078
Where?

279
00:36:02,317 --> 00:36:04,285
There, on the branch

280
00:36:04,953 --> 00:36:06,319
Which one?

281
00:36:06,354 --> 00:36:09,585
There! Behind the trunk.

282
00:36:09,925 --> 00:36:12,257
I don't see it.

283
00:36:13,261 --> 00:36:15,126
What's that?

284
00:36:15,964 --> 00:36:19,422
That’s a highway they’re building.

285
00:36:21,837 --> 00:36:24,106
We will loose a good chunk of the park.

286
00:36:24,141 --> 00:36:25,906
That's too bad.

287
00:36:25,941 --> 00:36:28,739
Well, it's complicated.

288
00:36:29,611 --> 00:36:32,171
Are you a “Chilean Chilean”?

289
00:36:32,247 --> 00:36:33,214
Yes!

290
00:36:33,348 --> 00:36:35,578
You don't look Chilean.

291
00:36:35,684 --> 00:36:38,567
Because of...
the way you walk

292
00:36:38,602 --> 00:36:41,451
...like stepping on eggs, nervous.

293
00:36:42,324 --> 00:36:45,125
And how do Chilean women walk?

294
00:36:45,160 --> 00:36:48,762
I don't know, firmly, looking forward.

295
00:36:51,797 --> 00:36:55,104
Do you know that Silvio Rodriguez's
song the one about the brothers?

296
00:36:55,639 --> 00:36:57,162
Yes... no, how was it?

297
00:37:00,642 --> 00:37:03,202
Well, there were three brothers.

298
00:37:04,446 --> 00:37:08,246
The first one always walked
looking down.

299
00:37:10,618 --> 00:37:16,550
So his neck got stuck and he was
never able to look forward again.

300
00:37:16,792 --> 00:37:20,228
The second one... looked forward...

301
00:37:22,297 --> 00:37:25,562
... but he was always tripping on
stones.

302
00:37:26,434 --> 00:37:30,530
And the other one looked up and down
like undecided.

303
00:37:31,039 --> 00:37:33,173
Right. Which one's me?

304
00:37:33,208 --> 00:37:37,179
The last one.
The one always changing the gaze.

305
00:37:37,214 --> 00:37:38,476
One eye for each side.

306
00:37:39,481 --> 00:37:40,647
So?

307
00:37:40,682 --> 00:37:41,910
So what?

308
00:37:42,350 --> 00:37:44,841
How does it end?
What happens to that one?

309
00:37:45,420 --> 00:37:49,220
Nothing. He remains confused forever.

310
00:37:50,959 --> 00:37:56,097
Finally they all do badly.
It's like a fable

311
00:37:56,132 --> 00:37:58,588
