316
00:38:12,883 --> 00:38:15,339
No, it's just like that.

317
00:38:16,952 --> 00:38:19,011
Do we know each other?

318
00:38:19,754 --> 00:38:23,315
I don't know you.
You might know me.

319
00:38:24,025 --> 00:38:26,361
Were you on TV?
You were an actor!

320
00:38:26,396 --> 00:38:28,128
Once I got offered a...

321
00:38:28,163 --> 00:38:31,223
You were a singer!
Yes, you were a singer!

322
00:38:31,967 --> 00:38:33,969
How was your name?
Don't tell me...

323
00:38:34,004 --> 00:38:35,001
Orlando.

324
00:38:35,036 --> 00:38:37,038
Of course!
Don't tell me your last name...

325
00:38:37,073 --> 00:38:38,205
Palma.

326
00:38:38,240 --> 00:38:42,199
Orlando Palma, of course.
You were very famous.

327
00:38:42,310 --> 00:38:45,074
You had that song everybody knew...

328
00:38:45,146 --> 00:38:46,947
“Vanity” you mean.

329
00:38:46,982 --> 00:38:49,542
That was the best known.

330
00:38:49,985 --> 00:38:53,182
It was almost the only one people knew.

331
00:38:53,488 --> 00:38:55,080
How was it?

332
00:38:59,461 --> 00:39:03,365
Alpha Sierra to Oscar Papa,
do you copy?

333
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:04,598
I can't remember...

334
00:39:04,633 --> 00:39:07,165
Oscar Papa here,
go ahead Alfa Sierra.

335
00:39:07,200 --> 00:39:09,698
If you sing a bit
I’ll remember right away.

336
00:39:19,748 --> 00:39:21,545
What do you want?

337
00:39:22,050 --> 00:39:26,544
let's see... milk, coffee, and bread

338
00:39:27,722 --> 00:39:30,125
I have some avocados.

339
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:32,923
Ripe... Creamy

340
00:39:33,962 --> 00:39:38,199
A bit expensive, but they're worth it.
Want some?

341
00:39:38,234 --> 00:39:39,223
Sure.

342
00:39:39,868 --> 00:39:42,837
Susana! Bring some avocados!

343
00:39:43,271 --> 00:39:46,240
Don't yell at me,
I have a headache.

344
00:39:47,309 --> 00:39:48,775
Bring avocados.

345
00:39:48,810 --> 00:39:51,643
You go, I don't know how to pick them.

346
00:39:52,647 --> 00:39:55,775
Sell some bread to the lady then.

347
00:40:03,224 --> 00:40:04,589
Four.

348
00:40:13,835 --> 00:40:15,704
Did you arrive today?

349
00:40:15,739 --> 00:40:17,171
Yes, yesterday.

350
00:40:17,706 --> 00:40:19,606
From Santiago?

351
00:40:20,241 --> 00:40:22,242
Santiago is beautiful.

352
00:40:22,277 --> 00:40:25,245
I got my wisdom teeth pulled out there.

353
00:40:25,280 --> 00:40:28,647
I have an aunt there,
in EI Bosque, you know?

354
00:40:28,783 --> 00:40:32,583
Yes, I mean not specifically but yes.

355
00:40:34,589 --> 00:40:36,556
Do you live here?

356
00:40:36,591 --> 00:40:39,992
In Molina, but in the summer
we work here.

357
00:40:40,228 --> 00:40:42,564
And what do you do in Santiago?

358
00:40:42,599 --> 00:40:44,498
I’m a biochemist.

359
00:40:45,834 --> 00:40:47,801
You work in a lab?

360
00:40:47,836 --> 00:40:50,972
You mix things in jars,
reactions and stuff?

361
00:40:51,007 --> 00:40:53,304
Precisely. And you both?

362
00:40:53,441 --> 00:40:58,936
Susana studies hairdressing
and I study accounting

363
00:40:59,914 --> 00:41:02,917
You are with that blond guy, right?

364
00:41:02,952 --> 00:41:05,920
