373
00:41:21,836 --> 00:41:23,721
From Oslo?

374
00:41:23,756 --> 00:41:25,606
I don't know.

375
00:41:28,376 --> 00:41:29,502
2.800

376
00:41:47,729 --> 00:41:52,067
Sun block! Did anybody bring sun block?

377
00:41:52,102 --> 00:41:53,534
No.

378
00:41:53,701 --> 00:41:55,969
It's not that sunny, Mari please.

379
00:41:56,004 --> 00:41:58,173
Don't start daddy, I already explained.

380
00:41:58,208 --> 00:42:01,108
Fine, I’ll go.

381
00:42:04,679 --> 00:42:07,313
It's not that sunny,
it's ridiculous.

382
00:42:07,348 --> 00:42:08,749
It's because of the hole.

383
00:42:08,750 --> 00:42:13,150
My field guide says
the hole is huge here.

384
00:42:14,923 --> 00:42:16,222
The hole!

385
00:42:16,257 --> 00:42:17,849
The ozone hole.

386
00:42:18,326 --> 00:42:20,995
Where are you from?

387
00:42:21,030 --> 00:42:22,796
From Norway.

388
00:42:22,831 --> 00:42:28,770
I have a friend from Norway.
He's called Olsen Forden.

389
00:42:35,643 --> 00:42:37,201
Sun block!

390
00:42:40,014 --> 00:42:42,715
Is your husband like that gentleman?

391
00:42:42,750 --> 00:42:46,709
No... yes, I don't know.
He's different.

392
00:42:47,922 --> 00:42:49,189
In what?

393
00:42:49,224 --> 00:42:51,522
He's more interesting

394
00:42:51,860 --> 00:42:53,555
More handsome?

395
00:42:57,765 --> 00:43:00,393
He's smart, he's funny.

396
00:43:00,835 --> 00:43:03,463
And why aren’t you with him then?

397
00:43:03,805 --> 00:43:06,899
I don't think that’s an issue you can
help me with

398
00:43:07,041 --> 00:43:08,941
All right...

399
00:43:11,312 --> 00:43:16,017
I can't help because I’m not an adult?
Because I don't have kids?

400
00:43:16,052 --> 00:43:18,620
No, because it’s a complicated
issue for anyone.

401
00:43:18,655 --> 00:43:20,555
You are saying
I’m an adult then?

402
00:43:20,590 --> 00:43:21,715
Yes...

403
00:43:23,091 --> 00:43:29,089
My girlfriend would tell me everyday
that I’m like an immature boy.

404
00:43:31,499 --> 00:43:33,399
That word makes me laugh.

405
00:43:33,535 --> 00:43:35,435
Like an unripe fruit.

406
00:43:35,670 --> 00:43:38,969
I told her she was a rotten fruit.

407
00:43:39,874 --> 00:43:41,842
I don't have that word in Norway.

408
00:43:41,910 --> 00:43:43,070
Mature?

409
00:43:43,545 --> 00:43:46,571
How is to be mature?

410
00:43:47,115 --> 00:43:49,675
Mature, like...

411
00:43:50,050 --> 00:43:51,050
...like the fruit.

412
00:43:51,051 --> 00:43:56,685
Like when fruit is ready to be
eaten, it is like being ready for life.

413
00:43:58,359 --> 00:44:01,442
Completely developed...

414
00:44:01,443 --> 00:44:04,525
Emotionally, mentally.

415
00:44:05,934 --> 00:44:10,838
Basically, it's knowing what you want,
what you like and don't like...

416
00:44:10,873 --> 00:44:12,372
...being calm.

417
00:44:12,407 --> 00:44:14,875
Being old essentially.

418
00:44:15,777 --> 00:44:18,905
I think it's harder than being old.

419
00:44:19,013 --> 00:44:23,416
But when you are mature
it's all over, then what?

420
00:44:24,652 --> 00:44:28,247
Then... I don't know...

421
00:44:28,323 --> 00:44:32,817
...enjoy adult life, supposedly.

422
00:44:34,729 --> 00:44:39,901
Like fruit... you're there,
hanging from the tree...

423
00:44:39,936 --> 00:44:44,235
...you're just enjoying the sun.

424
00:44:45,240 --> 00:44:48,186
Then you begin to decay.

425
00:44:48,187 --> 00:44:54,080
The birds start picking on you...

426
00:44:55,250 --> 00:45:00,278
...you fall to the ground,
then tissues start to decompose and...

427
00:45:00,688 --> 00:45:03,090
...I don't know.

428
00:45:03,125 --> 00:45:05,492
You bite your nails!

429
00:45:39,627 --> 00:45:41,322
Hi.

430
00:45:59,247 --> 00:46:02,705
I have a confession to make.

431
00:46:05,153 --> 00:46:06,620
Sure?

432
00:46:08,456 --> 00:46:10,321
If you don't want,
I won't tell you.

433
00:46:10,491 --> 00:46:13,255
Don't tell me if you don't want to.

434
00:46:14,729 --> 00:46:19,063
I had a boyfriend.
Just once, in Norway.

435
00:46:19,934 --> 00:46:21,162
What happened?

436
00:46:21,502 --> 00:46:22,662
He left me.

437
00:46:22,837 --> 00:46:24,998
He left you? Why?

438
00:46:25,573 --> 00:46:27,632
I became jealous and I hit him

439
00:46:27,842 --> 00:46:30,868
You hit him?
I don't believe you.

440
00:46:31,212 --> 00:46:34,375
For real. A punch like this.

441
00:46:34,515 --> 00:46:36,710
I can't imagine you hitting anybody.

442
00:46:37,018 --> 00:46:42,957
It was the first time. Did you know
the fist hurts a lot? Hitting hurts.

443
00:46:43,257 --> 00:46:46,715
That's fine, it's fair that it hurts.

444
00:46:47,228 --> 00:46:48,796
Have you hit anybody?

445
00:46:48,831 --> 00:46:50,263
No

446
00:46:50,298 --> 00:46:52,433
And have you been hit?

447
00:46:52,468 --> 00:46:53,900
No.

448
00:47:00,041 --> 00:47:02,441
You probably haven't fallen off a bike.

449
00:47:02,543 --> 00:47:06,775
I’m not going to compete for who
has suffered more, Ulrik.

450
00:47:07,382 --> 00:47:09,873
That's because you're mature.

451
00:47:10,151 --> 00:47:14,451
Don't mess with me! I am trying to rest.

452
00:47:14,889 --> 00:47:16,857
Did you get mad?

453
00:48:01,302 --> 00:48:03,964
Alpha Sierra to Oscar Papa,
do you copy?

454
00:48:04,672 --> 00:48:06,374
Oscar Papa why don't you answer?

455
00:48:06,409 --> 00:48:08,257
Turn off the radio!

456
00:48:08,292 --> 00:48:10,106
Don't be do loud!

457
00:48:13,014 --> 00:48:14,747
I’m bored!

458
00:48:14,782 --> 00:48:16,977
You left me all alone here!

459
00:48:27,795 --> 00:48:29,746
I can come back later.

460
00:48:29,781 --> 00:48:31,698
- No, go ahead.
- Thanks.

461
00:48:52,520 --> 00:48:56,989
Look, Orlando finished the
translation. It goes...

462
00:48:57,024 --> 00:49:00,894
When routine bites and we run out
of ambition,

463
00:49:00,895 --> 00:49:04,765
and resentment triumphs...

464
00:49:04,800 --> 00:49:09,136
...emotions get stuck and we are
changing, taking different routes.

465
00:49:09,171 --> 00:49:12,128
Then, love, love...

466
00:49:12,206 --> 00:49:14,342
Love will tear us apart.

467
00:49:14,377 --> 00:49:16,309
Love, love...

468
00:49:16,344 --> 00:49:19,802
Well like that, 4 times,
it's the chorus.

469
00:49:21,249 --> 00:49:23,050
It’s sad, isn't it?

470
00:49:23,085 --> 00:49:24,016
What?

471
00:49:24,018 --> 00:49:26,646
That love always tears you apart.

472
00:49:26,921 --> 00:49:28,286
I like it.

473
00:49:28,422 --> 00:49:30,390
Because it has never happened to you.

474
00:49:30,491 --> 00:49:32,584
No? What about Jose?

475
00:49:33,094 --> 00:49:35,595
You always said that José was a fool.

476
00:49:35,630 --> 00:49:39,828
He was a fool, but love teared us
apart anyway.

477
00:49:40,234 --> 00:49:42,664
One thing has nothing
to do with the other.

478
00:49:42,665 --> 00:49:44,694
I was in love.

479
00:49:46,707 --> 00:49:49,642
I couldn't fall in love with a fool.

480
00:49:50,278 --> 00:49:52,178
Because you're a coward.

481
00:49:53,214 --> 00:49:56,945
It's much more dangerous to fall in love
with fools because you don't get them.

482
00:49:57,718 --> 00:50:00,084
They are pure mystery.

483
00:50:01,522 --> 00:50:05,458
Like riding a horse,
but with your eyes closed.

484
00:50:05,593 --> 00:50:08,221
That's stupid.
Why would anybody want that?

485
00:50:08,529 --> 00:50:12,216
Because it's exciting.
It's risky.

486
00:50:12,817 --> 00:50:15,903
That's the point! That's
how love should be.

487
00:50:15,938 --> 00:50:18,064
You are such a fool, Susana.

488
00:50:18,172 --> 00:50:19,972
But that's what your song says, right?

489
00:50:20,007 --> 00:50:23,602
Right, but it’s a sad song and
you're saying it as a good thing.

490
00:50:28,015 --> 00:50:30,984
Who's in the shower?

491
00:51:24,305 --> 00:51:26,500
What a surprise.

492
00:51:27,575 --> 00:51:31,033
Where are you!
You disappeared.

493
00:51:33,881 --> 00:51:36,714
Well, I changed plans.

494
00:51:39,320 --> 00:51:42,254
Great that you recovered
your sense of humor

495
00:51:42,289 --> 00:51:46,316
I thought you were still crying over
the steering wheel.

496
00:51:49,830 --> 00:51:52,958
Sorry, I didn't mean to say that.

497
00:51:54,335 --> 00:51:57,827
Sorry, I told you already, it's enough.

498
00:51:59,807 --> 00:52:03,265
I’m so annoying, I know.

499
00:52:09,917 --> 00:52:13,876
In “Siete Tazas”, do you know it?
It’s beautiful.

500
00:52:18,459 --> 00:52:22,020
Yes, I mean, more or less by myself.

501
00:52:22,963 --> 00:52:26,922
Do you know who is
the park ranger here? Guess.

502
00:52:30,905 --> 00:52:34,864
Well, if you're not interested
I won't tell you.

503
00:52:39,346 --> 00:52:43,305
No, don't hang up, let's talk at least.

504
00:53:05,072 --> 00:53:06,539
Honey!

505
00:53:12,480 --> 00:53:14,778
Ximena, how are you?

506
00:53:15,449 --> 00:53:16,916
I’m fine.

507
00:53:24,592 --> 00:53:27,026
Sure, don't worry.

508
00:53:27,628 --> 00:53:30,153
OK, you have my computer.

509
00:53:31,031 --> 00:53:33,727
... go to shared files.

510
00:53:40,474 --> 00:53:43,932
... folder... Time.

511
00:53:46,247 --> 00:53:51,617
Open there, the file is called MDS final
...that one.

512
00:53:51,752 --> 00:53:54,448
Right - click there..

